article.headline: Youngstown State 72, Duquesne 51
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Keston Roberts scored 24 points and Quin Humphrey had 20 points and 11 rebounds to help Youngstown State beat Duquesne 72-51 on Saturday. The Penguins (2-6) opened the game with an 11-2 run and never trailed. They led by as many as 23 late in the second half. John Barber also had 13 points for Youngstown State, which outrebounded the Dukes 36-26 and held them to 38.5 percent shooting. The Penguins connected on 19 of 26 free throws, compared with 5-for-6 for Duquesne. DeVario Hudson led the Dukes (1-6) with 15 points and Jack Higgins finished with 13. Bryant McAllister scored 10 points. Humphrey scored 11 points in the first half as the Penguins raced out to a 40-23 lead at the break. The Dukes committed 10 turnovers before intermission. Derrick Harris passed for six assists and also had two steals for the Penguins, who shot 48 percent from the field.
